content.description: This climb was a pleasant surprise for me. Sit start and find sidepulls as low as you can. work your right hand up until you find the crux which is a cross to a good sloppy crimp. Then match the smile faced crimp and top out. avoid the sapling growing in the crack at the top when topping out. Once at the top give it a good victory toot.
content.protection: 2 pads. Try not to fall in the river.
content.location: See the victory boulder page on how to get there.

content.description: Find obvious undercling flake and left hand side pull next to it. Hike your feet up high and reach/jump to hero jug above it and top out. Short and sweet.Â
content.location: To the left of Victory Toot

content.description: First climbable boulder along the left side of the river. The landing has been built out with two planks of wood. It looks sketchy but is quite safe in my experience. This boulder for sure has more climbs on it but so far I've found 2 on it. There is at least one more.
